        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        The 2025 Democracy Perception Index says the global view of the United States <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-14-may-25-spotlight-h1-1-has-sharply-declined" target="_blank">has sharply declined</a> since Donald Trump returned to the presidency. This trend is especially notable in the European Union, where Trump's hostile comments have worsened opinions. This decline reflects Trump‚Äôs global popularity. His current favorability ratings are lower than those of Vladimir Putin and Xi Jinping.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         Meanwhile, China has surpassed the US in global favorability for the first time. It enjoys positive views in nearly every area except Europe, which remains cautious toward China and Russia. </p>  
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         Russia, while still seen negatively for its war in Ukraine, is gradually improving its image, especially outside Europe. Israel has the worst international reputation in the survey due to rising backlash over its actions in Gaza. Even traditional allies like Germany are becoming more uneasy, especially after ICC arrest warrants for Israeli leaders over alleged war crimes.</p>  
