          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Russia found guilty</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
         <strong>Summary: A UN body found that Russia failed to uphold an international air law that resulted in the MH17 tragedy.</strong>
         </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          The United Nations‚Äô aviation agency <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-14-may-25-spotlight-h2-3-found-russia-guilty" target="_blank">found Russia guilty</a> of downing Malaysia Airlines Flight 17 while it flew over Ukraine in July 2014. The flight was shot down over Eastern Ukraine amid the armed conflict between pro-Russian rebels and Ukrainian military forces. The council concluded that Russia violated the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-14-may-25-spotlight-h2-4-chicago-convention" target="_blank">Chicago Convention</a>, which prohibits the use of weapons against civilian aircraft. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          In 2016, a Dutch-led investigation concluded that a Russian-supplied Buk missile system shot down the plane. The Netherlands and Australia brought the case to the International Civil Aviation Organization (ICAO) in 2022. Though Russia denied the allegations, open-source evidence and numerous international investigations have assembled the pattern of events that led to the downing of the plane.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
       Reparations are on the table. Dutch FM Caspar Veldkamp and Australian FM Penny Wong urge Russia to negotiate and accept responsibility. ICAO may recommend that Russia pay damages, but the detailed reasoning behind the council‚Äôs decision is yet to be published. </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
